WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.130 --> 00:00:06.460
I was a young black male, 

00:00:06.460 --> 00:00:11.160
just recently released from prison.  There's not a lot of people that's gonna hire me.

00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:16.029
When I filed for divorce I found myself
basically out of a job as well because I worked

00:00:16.029 --> 00:00:17.190
for the family business

00:00:17.190 --> 00:00:21.340
When I hit my chin...I threw my neck back...
and

00:00:23.369 --> 00:00:26.290
next thing I knew I was a C5 quadriplegic.

00:00:26.290 --> 00:00:29.680
I found myself in a position that I was
looking for employment

00:00:29.680 --> 00:00:32.460
and um

00:00:32.460 --> 00:00:35.610
I was at an age where is pretty scary

00:00:35.610 --> 00:00:37.400
to be really honest with you.

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:46.900
I came from a rough lifestyle. I mean, my mom was a crackhead. Pops was absentee and wasn't there for me. So I grew up basically, in the streets.

00:00:47.600 --> 00:00:52.100
What changed in my life is that by me moving to Milwaukee and a new state and new environment, 

00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:56.350
I knew I can do better than what I was
doing.

00:00:56.350 --> 00:00:59.960
When you see our billboards in your
local neighborhoods that say when you donate

00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:04.600
we train people work that's really what
Goodwill is all about.

00:01:10.530 --> 00:01:13.990
When people think of Goodwill they most
often think about our Goodwill Store and

00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:17.300
Donations Centers and that's very
important because it is our economic

00:01:17.300 --> 00:01:17.980
engine.

00:01:19.960 --> 00:01:24.549
When you donate and you shop at Goodwill the income is then invested in our training

00:01:24.549 --> 00:01:28.360
programs and employment opportunities
for individuals that are disadvantaged

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:29.229
disabled

00:01:29.229 --> 00:01:31.600
or they may be dislocated workers.

00:01:35.390 --> 00:01:39.080
We serve people from all walks of life
you don't have to be referred to us

00:01:39.080 --> 00:01:42.600
it doesn't matter what your income level
if you're seeking training or a job

00:01:42.600 --> 00:01:46.250
you can come to a Workforce Connection
Center we'll help you with your resume

00:01:46.250 --> 00:01:49.619
we'll help you with your interviews but
more importantly we can connect you with

00:01:49.619 --> 00:01:50.409
employers.

00:01:50.409 --> 00:01:55.890
Being unemployed is, is scary, and I think
when you surround yourself with people

00:01:55.890 --> 00:01:57.070
that are upbeat

00:01:57.070 --> 00:02:01.479
and all solution-driven and creative
in ways on how you can get out of

00:02:01.479 --> 00:02:03.500
this dilemma, that's very uplifting.

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:07.950
Going to Goodwill, provided me with resume writing skills, the

00:02:07.950 --> 00:02:11.250
practice interviews, all, all the little essential 

00:02:11.250 --> 00:02:15.160
things that they did for me help bring

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:18.540
confidence to who I am.  Goodwill gave me a chance

00:02:18.540 --> 00:02:22.800
by giving me skills that I already had

00:02:22.800 --> 00:02:26.160
but they...they brought them out more.  If you think you don't have the

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:26.880
skills

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:31.590
the find them in you.  It was a godsend for me. They give you able to have skills to work

00:02:32.069 --> 00:02:36.510
at retail period.  And I didn't have a
medical background no medical

00:02:36.510 --> 00:02:39.690
training whatsoever other than what I
took in high school

00:02:39.690 --> 00:02:42.400
the lessons learned there were phenomenal.  

00:02:45.200 --> 00:02:49.110
Goodwill Great Lakes is very
important to our organization

00:02:49.110 --> 00:02:53.830
and our mission.  I say Great Lakes...a great job
for you

00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:58.000
if you're looking for a great job and good
pay too.

